headline.main: CHUNGKING ACCLAIM WELCOMES WILLKIE; His Airliner Dodges Japanese War Planes -- Their Hunt 'Flatters' Him, He Says CHUNGKING CHEERS WILLKIE ARRIVAL

lead_paragraph: CHUNGKING, China, Oct. 2 -- Wendell L. Willkie arrived in the capital of Free China today with a jovial quip for the danger of Japanese aerial attack that was so real at one time that his 4,000-mile flight across Asia from Russia was delayed by a roving enemy scout plane.
